    <h2 id="ashwagandha-anxiety">How Ashwagandha Attacks Anxiety at Two Biological Levels</h2>

    <p>Ashwagandha (<em>Withania somnifera</em>) is classified as an adaptogen — a substance that helps the body adapt to stress by modulating the stress response rather than simply masking symptoms. For anxiety specifically, ashwagandha operates through two distinct biological mechanisms that make it uniquely effective: HPA axis cortisol regulation (hormonal) and GABAergic neurotransmitter modulation (neurochemical).</p>

