    </div>

    <p>The first mechanism — HPA axis regulation — addresses the hormonal root of chronic anxiety. The hypothalamic-pituitary-adrenal axis is the body's central stress command system. In chronic anxiety, this axis becomes dysregulated, producing elevated cortisol that perpetuates the anxiety cycle. KSM-66 ashwagandha reduces serum cortisol by modulating cortisol synthesis at the adrenal level, breaking the feedback loop that sustains chronic anxiety states.</p>

    <p>The second mechanism — GABAergic activity — provides the more immediate calming effect. Withanolides, the primary bioactive compounds in ashwagandha, have been shown to bind to GABA-A receptors as positive allosteric modulators. This means they enhance the brain's natural GABA signaling without replacing it — producing calming effects without the dependence risk associated with direct GABA agonists like benzodiazepines.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Cortisol reduction: 30%</strong>
        <p>KSM-66 at 600mg/day reduced serum cortisol by 30% in a 60-day RCT. This addresses the hormonal driver of chronic anxiety — the sustained cortisol elevation that keeps the nervous system in fight-or-flight mode.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>GABA modulation</strong>
        <p>Withanolides act as positive allosteric modulators at GABA-A receptors, enhancing natural GABA signaling without direct agonism. This produces calming without sedation, dependence, or withdrawal.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>KSM-66: 24 clinical studies</strong>
